Renal transplantation has been established as a life-saving procedure for 
patients with ESRD. Deceased donor kidneys convey variable life expectancies for 
recipients. However, limited information is available to guide patients and 
patient advocates concerning the appropriateness to list for expanded criteria 
donations (ECD). Half-lives for wait-listed transplant candidates were estimated 
from the time of ESRD onset on the basis of recipient age, primary diagnosis, 
and organ quality using survival models. In addition, we evaluated the 
likelihood of candidates' receiving a transplant on the basis of age and other 
characteristics by duration of waiting time. Older patients (65+) had longer 
